1:
Praise Yahweh.
\q Praise the name of Yahweh.
\q Praise him, you servants of Yahweh,
\q
2:
you who stand in Yahweh's house,
\q in the courtyards of the house of our God.
4:
For Yahweh has chosen Jacob for himself,
\q Israel as his possession.
5:
I know that Yahweh is great,
\q that our Lord is above all gods.
\q
6:
Whatever Yahweh desires, he does
\q in heaven, on earth, in the seas and all the ocean depths.
7:
He brings the clouds from far away,
\q making lightning bolts accompany the rain
\q and bringing the wind out of his storehouse.
8:
He killed the firstborn of Egypt,
\q both of man and animals.
\q
9:
He sent signs and wonders into your midst, Egypt,
\q against Pharaoh and all his servants.
10:
He attacked many nations
\q and killed mighty kings,
\q
11:
Sihon king of the Amorites
\q and Og king of Bashan
\q and all the kingdoms of Canaan.
12:
He gave us their land as an inheritance,
\q an inheritance to Israel his people.
\q
14:
For Yahweh defends his people
\q and has compassion on his servants.
15:
The nations' idols are silver and gold,
\q the work of men's hands.
\q
17:
they have ears, but they do not hear,
\q nor is there breath in their mouths.
\q
18:
Those who make them are like them,
\q as is everyone who trusts in them.
21:
Blessed be Yahweh in Zion,
\q he who lives in Jerusalem.
\q Praise Yahweh.
